    <AbstractNarration>The research is directed toward understanding the effects of electron correlation on photoionization, photodetachment and electron scattering. A variety of approaches are used, close-coupling, R-matrix theory and the random phase approximation. Part of the research is dedicated to understanding these processes when atoms are confined such as atoms trapped in fullerenes.</AbstractNarration>
